records.addlTxt:
Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED-

Court ordered defendant to serve 7 MONTHS in the House of Correction; straight time.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 12 MONTHS with the following conditions:
1) Court ordered 45 days of condition time in the House of Correction imposed but STAYED to be used at the discretion of the agent;
2) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
3) Pay restitution in the amount of $946.73 to be paid to Nordstrom Rack. Restitution to be paid FIRST before all costs, fees and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
4) Defendant to make payments of at least $50.00 per month towards restitution, costs, fees and surcharges;
5) No contact with any Nordstrom store;
6) Maintain current employment unless enrolled full time in educational or vocational programming;
7) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;

If revoked, defendant may have release for work if employed at the time of revocation. 

If revoked, defendant may participate in vocational training or educational programming and may attend the Day Reporting Center.

If revoked, Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
